        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 1:30PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 129 PM CDT/1229 PM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm over Nadine, or 10 miles south of Hobbs, moving south at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hobbs, Monument, Nadine, and Lea County Regional Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
